cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

The paper deals with image classification using neural networks and focuses on interpretability of the model. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the tradeoff between restricting global image context and classification error, which falls under the category of machine learning and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also mentions the use of domain experts to compare the features selected by PatchNet, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence, making cs.AI another likely category. The paper also discusses the use of visual heatmap representations, which falls under the category of natural language processing and computer graphics, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.MM (Multimedia) other possible categories.
